{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01MVJd9zT7BE3t8oSEVUAuXG","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The same error occurs when using `POST /api/events` with a timestamp containing 'Z'. So the timestamp format issue (`Z` suffix not supported) is a pre-existing bug in the system, not something introduced by F15's seed.ts.\n\nAlso, the properties also have double-escaping issue: `{\\\\\\\"page\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"/home\\\\\\\"}` - which shows the properties are being double-escaped.\n\nLet me look at the `insertEvent` function in `src/lib/identity.ts` to understand how it handles timestamps and properties.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3293,"cache_read_input_tokens":55875,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3293},"output_tokens":32,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fc8bcdff-58cd-47ca-9de9-d42a328d887e","uuid":"136650be-594f-4092-9b9a-7f06da21661d"}
